      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (NIH, g/100L) is the same metric used in the regulatory submission and in the clinical hemolysis threshold specification. Secondary QoIs (volumetric flow rate, pressure head, velocity profiles) are all directly relevant to the intended use. The hemolysis power-law integration tracks the Lagrangian stress history of fluid elements, directly corresponding to the biological mechanism of red blood cell damage. Gradation 4 achieved.",
