      "rationale": "Model form selection justified by systematic comparison of turbulence models (SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, RSM) against PIV data; SST k-ω selected based on lowest velocity RMS error (4.2% vs 6.8% and 8.1%). Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen–Wurzinger) justified by published meta-analysis of red blood cell damage thresholds; limitations documented and within COU operating range. Non-Newtonian blood rheology assessed and shown to contribute <3% to NIH at VAD operating conditions, justifying Newtonian assumption. Gradation 4 achieved.",
